  "output": "That's fine — I have enough from `requirements.txt` (just `httpx` and `PyYAML`) to confirm there's no test tooling installed at all. Here's the full analysis.\n\n# Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\n**Current state: zero tests exist in this repo.** No `test_*.py` files, no `tests/` directory, no `pytest` in `requirements.txt`. Every one of the ~40 functions and the `Job`/`Store` classes below is completely unexercised. This is a bigger gap than a typical \"missing edge cases\" report — I've prioritized by risk (pure parsing logic first, since `fetchers.py`'s own docstring says it was designed to be unit-tested against mocked transports, then stateful/IO modules, then process-boundary code).\n\nFirst, the harness that doesn't exist yet:\n\n```python\n# requirements-dev.txt\npytest>=8.0\npytest-asyncio>=0.24\nrespx>=0.21          # httpx mock transport, for fetchers.py\nfreezegun>=1.5        # for datetime-dependent code (models.parse_posted_at, filters.cutoff, agent._iso_now)\n```\n\n```python\n# conftest.py\nimport pytest\nfrom models import Job\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef make_job():\n    def _make(**kw):\n        defaults = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                         title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\")\n        return Job(**{**defaults, **kw})\n    return _make\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. `models.py` — highest ROI, zero deps, untested\n\n| Function | Gap |\n|---|---|\n| `parse_posted_at` | No coverage of any branch: empty string, ms-epoch, sec-epoch, ISO with `Z`, ISO with offset, unparseable prose (\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") |\n| `Job.key` / `.posted_dt` / `.content_hash` / `.to_row` | Not tested at all |\n\n**Edge cases missing:**\n- Negative epoch string (`s.lstrip(\"-\").isdigit()`)\n- Boundary at exactly `1_000_000_000_000` (ms vs sec cutoff)\n- `content_hash` changes when `title`/`location`/`url`/`department` change but **not** when `salary_range`/`posted_at`/`raw` change — this asymmetry is a designed inv