        "content": "\nThe deterministic half (`cmd_db_new`'s group-truncation logic, `_normalize_ats`) is high-value and easy to test in isolation. The subprocess half needs mocking.\n\n**Key missing edge case:** `cmd_db_new`'s truncation must only cut at `first_seen` group boundaries (never split a timestamp-group), per the inline comment — this is subtle and completely unverified.\n\n```python\n",
