        "title": "Priority order",
        "content": "1. **`models.py` + `filters.py`** — zero-dependency pure logic, cheapest to test, and `content_hash`'s field-selection invariant is silently load-bearing for dedup correctness.\n2. **`fetchers.py` parsers** — highest bug surface (16 ATS integrations), each is a thin defensive parser against undocumented/shifting external JSON; a schema drift here fails silently (empty string fields) rather than crashing, so only tests catch it.\n3. **`store.py`** — dedup/migration correctness; a bug here means duplicate notifications or lost history.\n4. **`pipeline.py`** — the only true integration seam; currently nothing proves fetch→filter→dedup→notify actually wires together.\n5. **`notify.py`** — env-var gating, mock `httpx.post`/`smtplib.SMTP`, never hit real endpoints.\n6. **`agent.py`/`cli.py`** — deterministic parts (`_normalize_ats`, `cmd_db_new` truncation) first; subprocess/exec parts last since they need the most mocking for the least behavioral risk.",
